<h1>O(2)-Hopf Calculator</h1>

<p>
This web calculator accompanies my work on cubic O(2)-Hopf normal-form
coefficients for polynomial PDE systems.
</p>

<p>
The user enters the Fourier symbol of the linear operator and the
multi-index representation of the polynomial nonlinearity. The app computes
the coefficients zeta and xi, checks structural assumptions where possible,
and classifies the result into the transition regions used in the paper.
</p>

<p>
<strong>Note.</strong> The app is a computational companion and
hypothesis-checking aid. Finite numerical checks over modes do not replace
the analytic assumptions in the paper.
</p>

